        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Move cron store/run-log JSON/SQLite conversion into focused codecs and keep core cron runtime on SQLite-backed rows.\n- Replace legacy runtime `notify`/global webhook fallback with explicit per-job delivery and announce-only completion webhooks.\n- Add doctor and startup migration coverage for legacy notify jobs, including modeless chat delivery, invalid webhook targets, and early SQLite row shapes.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/gateway/server-cron-notifications.test.ts src/gateway/server.cron.test.ts src/gateway/server-methods/cron.validation.test.ts src/cron/service/ops.test.ts src/cron/service.jobs.test.ts src/commands/doctor/cron/index.test.ts src/cron/normalize.test.ts src/cron/run-log.test.ts src/cron/store.test.ts -- --reporter=verbose`\n- `env -u OPENCLAW_TESTBOX pnpm check:changed --timed`\n- `pnpm docs:list`\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode branch --base origin/main`\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: cron runtime no longer relies on legacy `notify` plus `cron.webhook` fallback; doctor/startup migrate legacy jobs into explicit SQLite-backed delivery fields while preserving announce/chat delivery via completion webhooks.\n\nReal environment tested: local OpenClaw checkout on `codex/cron-sqlite-cleanups`, rebased on current `origin/main` (`724160b7eb`).\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: focused Vitest cron/gateway/doctor command above; changed gate above; docs list above; branch autoreview above.\n\nEvidence after fix: focused tests passed 3 Vitest shards; changed gate passed typecheck, lint, import cycles, and guard checks; branch autoreview reported no accepted/actionable findings.\n\nObserved result after fix: legacy notify jobs with chat delivery keep announce targets and gain a completion webhook, invalid legacy webhook targets fall back to configured `cron.webhook`, and early SQLite rows preserve modeless delivery without resurrecting stale webhook/chat fields.\n\nWhat was not tested: Crabbox/live provider lanes were not run; this change is covered by local focused runtime/migration tests plus changed gates.\n",
